        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>. <date>Apr. 12. 1849</date>.</p>
            <p>My dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">As it was important for me to be here<lb/> as soon as possible when
                I left home I passed<lb/> through your city in a hurry intending to stay<lb/> one
                day on my return home to see all the good<lb/> folks. I heard yesterday that the
                small pox<lb/> was in <persName>W. Newhouse'</persName> family. if that should
                be<lb/> so, it would be imprudent for me to haul up<lb/> at <persName>Aunt
                    Grace's</persName> If it would not be too much<lb/> out of your way and you can
                without any<lb/> inconvenience meet me at the Cars on<lb/>
                <date>Monday</date> next as I shall be ar. here at 9 0 Clk<lb/> in the morning. I
                should really like to know<lb/> if such is the fact in that event I shall<lb/>
                proceed home on <date>Sunday</date>
                <sic>otherways</sic>, I shall<lb/> remain that day and go home the next.<lb/> I
                should like to see <persName>Aunt Grace</persName> but cannot<lb/> run any such
                risque. <add>?</add> is quite well.<lb/> Remember me kindly to <persName>Ms.
                    Cozens</persName> &amp; family<lb/> and <persName>Florence'</persName>
                family.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Very truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Yrs.</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <hi rend="underline">
                    <persName role="author">Dani Judah</persName>
                </hi>
            </p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
